<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,370,2014]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,471,476,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Taxonomic comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="calotes" authorityName="calotes (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[483,659,476,500]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Calotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="calotes">
<emphasis box="[483,659,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Calotes calotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on specimens collected from ‘Zeylona’ (
<collectingCountry name="Sri Lanka" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<collectingRegion box="[1402,1436,476,501]" country="United Kingdom" name="Surrey" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Sri</collectingRegion>
Lanka
</collectingCountry>
). This species is currently known to commonly occur in the wet zones of 
<collectingCountry box="[1111,1225,511,536]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<collectingRegion box="[1111,1144,511,536]" country="United Kingdom" name="Surrey" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Sri</collectingRegion>
Lanka
</collectingCountry>
and dry zones of southern 
<collectingCountry box="[254,315,546,571]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">India</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[325,473,546,571]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refId="ref37909" refString="Smith, M. A. (1935) The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma; Reptilia and Amphibia. Fol. II. Sauria. Taylor and Francis, London, 440 pp." type="book">Smith (1935)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[815,991,546,571]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Nicobar Islands</collectingCountry>
but this was not included in later works (
<bibRefCitation box="[158,441,581,606]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refId="ref35996" refString="Harikrishnan, S., Vasudevan, K. &amp; Choudhury, B. C. (2010) A review of herpetofaunal descriptions and studies from Andaman and Nicobar Islands, with an updated checklist. In: Ramakrishna, Raghunathan, C. &amp; Sivaperuman, C. (Eds.), Recent Trends in Biodiversity of Andaman and Nicobar Islands. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata, pp 387 - 398." type="book chapter">
Harikrishnan 
<emphasis box="[314,372,581,605]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). The original description by Linnaeus was a two-line description, which was translated by 
<bibRefCitation box="[187,487,616,641]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refId="ref33690" refString="Amarasinghe, A. A. T., Manthey, U., Stockli, E., Ineich, I., Kullander, S. O., Tiedemann, F., McCarthy, C. &amp; Gabadage, D. E. (2009) The original descriptions and figures of Sri Lankan Agamid lizards (Squamata: Agamidae) of the 18 th and 19 th centuries. Taprobanica, 1 (1), 2 - 15. https: // doi. org / 10.4038 / tapro. v 1 i 1.2771" type="journal article">
Amarasinghe 
<emphasis box="[344,401,617,641]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
. Our analysis shows 1% genetic variance (in the 16S gene) between the 
<collectingRegion box="[1311,1344,616,641]" country="United Kingdom" name="Surrey" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Sri</collectingRegion>
Lankan and the Peninsular Indian population of 
<taxonomicName authority="calotes" authorityName="calotes (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[611,784,652,676]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Calotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="calotes">
<emphasis box="[611,784,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Calotes calotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This suggests that these species moved between the dry zones in Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[375,433,687,712]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[487,601,687,712]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<collectingRegion box="[487,520,687,712]" country="United Kingdom" name="Surrey" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Sri</collectingRegion>
Lanka
</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
